{% set whoCanUseThisService %}
## Who can use this service

You can use this service if you have, or think you might have, a TRN. You cannot use the service to find out someone else's TRN.

{% endset %}

{% set otherWaysToFindOutYourTrn%}
## Other ways to find out your TRN

### You may be able to find your TRN on a document

Your TRN may be shown on one of the following documents:

* payslip
* teacher pension statement
* teacher training records

The TRN has previously been known as a QTS, GTC, DfE, DfES or DCSF number.

---

### Find out your TRN by phone

> Call the Teaching Regulation Agency on 020 7593 5394.

Make sure you have your National Insurance number ready before you call.

{% endset %}

